  "prompt": "How do you know if you cat loves you?",
  "response": "Here are some signs that your cat loves you:\n\n1. Physical Affection\n- Purring when near you\n- Rubbing against you\n- Kneading or \"making biscuits\"\n- Cuddling or sleeping close to you\n- Slow blinking (cat kisses)\n\n2. Behavioral Signs\n- Following you around the house\n- Greeting you when you come home\n- Wanting to be in the same room as you\n- Showing you their belly (a sign of trust)\n- Bringing you \"gifts\" like toys or caught prey\n\n3. Communication\n- Meowing or chirping at you\n- Responding when you talk to them\n- Holding their tail up when you're around\n\n4. Body Language\n- Relaxed posture when near you\n- Not running away when you approach\n- Sitting facing towards you\n- Uncurled, relaxed tail\n\n5. Grooming\n- Licking you\n- Wanting to groom you (a social bonding behavior)\n\nRemember, cats show affection differently than dogs, and each cat has a unique personality. These signs can indicate your cat's love and trust.",
